metadata.name: solitude
metadata.description:
alone I wonder,
won't tomorrow come? 
i don't want to feel the pain anymore...

the ache of each hour slowly breaking through my skin is becoming routine...

i´m craving for the light to come back, 
cuz i haven't fit under my skin so far...

no more damage, i beg
it´s been so difficult just to stare...

if there´s a spark of light,
right now it seems so far...

- letter to myself during covid -

2160x2700
